The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, September 27, 2003 				 New software to speed up road projects
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Sept. 26: The ministry of road transport and highways today launched an information technology initiative to speed up projects to connect Delhi, Mumbai, Calcutta and Chennai.																								The initiative, called the national highways financial management information system, will be used by the ministry for improving management and co-ordination among the various agencies involved in construction and management of national highways.																								The software, developed by Bhilwara Infotech Ltd, will help the ministry to monitor the financial progress of projects throughout the country and give orders for release of funds in line with their actual requirement. 																								The web-based technology and internet-based system will also facilitate the provision of services to the engineering division and interested parties. 
